  • Classes
    Class
    Description
    BoardSpace
    The Monopoly gameboard consists of 40 spaces containing 28 properties (22 colored streets, four railway stations and two utilities), three Chance spaces, three Community Chest spaces, a Luxury Tax space, an Income Tax space, and the four corner squares: GO, (In) Jail/Just Visiting, Free Parking, and Go to Jail.
    ChanceSpace
    Represents a Chance space on the Monopoly board.
    CommunityChestSpace
    Represents a Community Chest space on the Monopoly board.
    FreeParkingSpace
    When a Player lands on this space, they incur no costs and remain on the space until their next dice roll.
    GoDirectlyToJailSpace
    When a player lands on this space, they must go directly to Jail, and on their way passing Go, do NOT collect $200.
    GoSpace
    Represents the Go space on the Monopoly board, the space from which all contestants begin the game.
    IncomeTaxSpace
    When a Player lands on this space, they must simply pay $200.
    JailSpace
    Represents the Jail space on the Monopoly board.
    LuxuryTaxSpace
    When a Player lands on this space, they must simply pay $100.
    PrivateBoardSpace<T extends Title>
    Instances of this class represent board spaces that can be privately held and thus purchased or sold by a player.
    PropertyBoardSpace
    An instance of this class is a property that can be owned, upon which houses and hotels may be built, and rent may be charged.
    PublicBoardSpace
    Instances of this class are those board spaces which are available to the public and thus cannot be bought or sold.
    RailroadBoardSpace
    An instance of this class represents one of the four Railroads available in the game.
    UtilityBoardSpace
    An instance of this class represents one of the two Utilities available in the game.
